This paper is about mining patterns from transaction databases, which is a common topic in the field of database systems (cs.DB). The paper proposes a new algorithm that considers user preferences and uses novel data structures to efficiently prune the search space, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data mining (cs.DM), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates the proposed algorithm on several datasets, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
